type":"*","value":[{"type":"{{","value":[["sleep"],["name=Alma Motel"],["url=http:\/\/www.almamotel.com"],["email="],["address=1575 Wright Ave."],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone = +1 989-463-1135"],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["checkin="],["checkout="],["content="]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"{{","value":[["sleep"],["name=Saravilla Bed & Breakfast"],["url=http:\/\/www.saravilla.com"],["email="],["address=633 N. State St."],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone = +1 989-463-4078"],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["checkin="],["checkout="],["content="]]}]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Go next"]},"\n\nAlma is a good starting point to head to the \"mitt\" of Michigan - aka ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Northern Michigan"]]},". Here are a few other places that aren't necessarily in Northern Michigan to get you out and away from Alma:\n\n",{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Mount Pleasant (Michigan)"],["Mount Pleasant"]]}," is 20 minute drive north from Alma. Mt. Pleasant is home to a Saginaw Chippewa Indian community, which throws a big pow-wow each year. "]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Lansing (Michigan)"],["Lansing"]]},", the state capital, is about an hour away via car. It's a college town, being home to Michigan State University, one off the biggest universities in the country. "]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Holland (Michigan)"],["Holland"]]},", Michigan, not the Netherlands! It's about a two hour drive. Go during the spring, to see all of the beautiful tulips and enjoy the town's Dutch heritage. "]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Muskegon"]]}," is two hours away and has clean lovely beaches with bike trails to visit on Lake Michigan. "]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Detroit"]]}," is also two hours away, and one of the most famous American cities - home to the car industry, revitalization, soul music, and more."]},"\n",{"type":"{{","value":[["rout